{"id":4648,"date":"2022-04-30T10:06:45","date_gmt":"2022-04-30T10:06:45","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/?p=4648"},"modified":"2023-04-03T10:45:21","modified_gmt":"2023-04-03T10:45:21","slug":"total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/","title":{"rendered":"How to Calculate The Total Cost of Buying A Flat in Bangalore"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Planning to buy a flat in Bangalore? Calculating the total cost of buying a flat is essential for a smooth purchasing experience &amp; a smooth move into the apartment.<\/p>\n<p>Our lives are filled with milestones \u2013 some that we achieve effortlessly such as entering adulthood, and some others that we create for ourselves, such as owning a home or a car. To turn the dream of owning a home into reality, we often plan by carefully budgeting our expenses so that we can make a larger down payment. But it doesn\u2019t end with just a down payment and an EMI. Homeowners end up shelling out more than just the cost of the apartment for other aspects. Here, we cover all the additional expenses that you may incur when buying your ideal home:<\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_63 ez-toc-wrap-left counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-custom ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title \" >Table of Contents<\/p>\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-toggle\"><\/span><\/div>\n<nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/#Aspects_That_Determine_The_Total_Cost_of_Buying_A_Flat_in_Bangalore\" title=\"Aspects That Determine The Total Cost of Buying A Flat in Bangalore\">Aspects That Determine The Total Cost of Buying A Flat in Bangalore<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/#Construction_Quality_Materials_Used\" title=\"Construction Quality &amp; Materials Used\">Construction Quality &amp; Materials Used<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/#Builders_Reputation\" title=\"Builders\u2019 Reputation\">Builders\u2019 Reputation<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/#Resale_Value\" title=\"Resale Value:\">Resale Value:<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/#Location_Value\" title=\"Location Value\">Location Value<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/#Amenities\" title=\"Amenities\">Amenities<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/#8_Additional_Expenses_You_Should_Consider_While_Calculating_the_Total_Cost_of_Buying_A_Flat_in_Bangalore_%E2%80%93\" title=\"8 Additional Expenses You Should Consider While Calculating the Total Cost of Buying A Flat in Bangalore: &#8211;\">8 Additional Expenses You Should Consider While Calculating the Total Cost of Buying A Flat in Bangalore: &#8211;<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/#Stamp_Duty_and_Registration_Charges\" title=\"Stamp Duty and Registration Charges\">Stamp Duty and Registration Charges<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-9\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/#Brokerage_Fee\" title=\"Brokerage Fee\">Brokerage Fee<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-10\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/#Parking_Cost\" title=\"Parking Cost\">Parking Cost<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-11\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/#Interior_Designs\" title=\"Interior Designs\">Interior Designs<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-12\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/#Goods_and_Service_Tax\" title=\"Goods and Service Tax\">Goods and Service Tax<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-13\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/#Preferential_Locality_Charge_PLC\" title=\"Preferential Locality Charge (PLC)\">Preferential Locality Charge (PLC)<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-14\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/#Maintenance_Cost_Deposit\" title=\"Maintenance Cost Deposit\">Maintenance Cost Deposit<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-15\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/#Miscellaneous_Charges\" title=\"Miscellaneous Charges\">Miscellaneous Charges<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-16\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/#Conclusion\" title=\"Conclusion:\">Conclusion:<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Aspects_That_Determine_The_Total_Cost_of_Buying_A_Flat_in_Bangalore\"><\/span><strong>Aspects That Determine The Total Cost of Buying A Flat in Bangalore<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>You and your friend may have invested in a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/2-bhk-flats-in-bangalore-for-sale\/\" rel=\"nofollow\">2 BHK apartment in Bengaluru<\/a>. But chances are that your friend may have paid far less than what you have due to various factors such as the builder\u2019s reputation, quality of construction, or the amenities that it comes with. Let\u2019s delve deeper into the total cost of a flat in Bangalore:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Construction_Quality_Materials_Used\"><\/span><strong>Construction Quality &amp; Materials Used<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>The quality of construction materials used to build your home has a direct impact on its price. Good quality homes come at a premium price but of course, this means fewer repairs and reconstruction in the years ahead.<\/li>\n<li>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Builders_Reputation\"><\/span><strong>Builders\u2019 Reputation<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Well-reputed builders will ensure good quality materials are used for construction. Therefore, as discussed in the previous point, such apartments will naturally be priced higher.<\/li>\n<li>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Resale_Value\"><\/span><strong>Resale Value:<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Usually, properties that are newer fetch a higher value. However, even those that have been well-maintained over the years, can also have higher value. Regular maintenance upgrades are also helpful in adding value to a property.<\/li>\n<li>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Location_Value\"><\/span><strong>Location Value<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Buildings in and around commercial and market areas have a higher value than those in isolated residential areas. Well-developed colonies, amidst reputed educational institutions, hospitals, and shopping plazas are evaluated at a higher price.<\/li>\n<li>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Amenities\"><\/span><strong>Amenities<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Values of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/city\/bengaluru\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" rel=\"nofollow\">apartments<\/a> with an array of modern amenities are estimated at a higher price. The property is valued based on the facilities associated with comfortable housing. Homebuyers look for apartments that offer basic facilities such as electricity connection, plumbing, and sewage treatment alongside recreational facilities such as parks, swimming pools, gyms, etc.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"8_Additional_Expenses_You_Should_Consider_While_Calculating_the_Total_Cost_of_Buying_A_Flat_in_Bangalore_%E2%80%93\"><\/span><strong>8 Additional Expenses You Should Consider While Calculating the Total Cost of Buying A Flat in Bangalore: &#8211;<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Stamp_Duty_and_Registration_Charges\"><\/span><strong>Stamp Duty and Registration Charges<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><img width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" class=\"size-full wp-image-4654 alignnone\" src=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/5.png\" alt=\"stamp-duty-registration-charges\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/5.png 1200w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/5-300x150.png 300w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/5-1024x512.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/5-768x384.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/><br \/>\nThis is one of those obvious expenses. To register the property under your name, the state government levies stamp duty which is about 5-7% of the property value, depending upon its value. Then, an additional 1% of the property value must be paid to the court as registration fees.<\/p>\n<p>So, if your property is estimated at Rs. 1 crore, the stamp duty is charged at 5% for property values above Rs. 45 lakh. That will work out to Rs. 5 lakh. The registration charge is an additional 1% of Rs. 1 crore, which is Rs. 1 lakh. In total, you will be shelling out Rs. 6 lakh on stamp duty and registration charges.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Must Read:<\/strong> <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/stamp-duty-and-property-registration-charges-in-bangalore\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" rel=\"nofollow\">Stamp Duty &amp; Registration Charges in Bangalore<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Brokerage_Fee\"><\/span><strong>Brokerage Fee<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><img width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4657\" src=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/2.png\" alt=\"Brokerage-fee\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/2.png 1200w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/2-300x150.png 300w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/2-1024x512.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/2-768x384.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/><br \/>\nIf you are zeroing on your ideal home with the help of a broker, then, needless to say, you will be shelling out a bit more. Both buyer and seller will pay an agreed-upon commission to the broker for carrying out smooth transactions.<\/p>\n<p>Assuming you went through a broker who charges a 2% commission on the property value, you\u2019d have to pay him Rs. 2 lakh on a property worth Rs. 1 crore.<\/li>\n<li>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Parking_Cost\"><\/span><strong>Parking Cost<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><img width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4658\" src=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/11.png\" alt=\"Parking-lot-Cost\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/11.png 1200w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/11-300x150.png 300w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/11-1024x512.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/11-768x384.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/>Apartments come with a host of amenities for all its residents, but if you own two cars, you will be allotted one parking slot only and you might have to pay extra for the other. This can range anywhere between Rs. 2-7 lakh per slot, depending upon the location of the slot as well as the apartment, in general.<\/p>\n<p>Let us assume that you are charged an additional Rs. 5 lakh + 12-18% GST towards the extra parking slot.<\/li>\n<li>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Interior_Designs\"><\/span><strong>Interior Designs<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-4659 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/15.png\" alt=\"interior-design-cost\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/15.png 1200w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/15-300x150.png 300w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/15-1024x512.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/15-768x384.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/>You must first set a budget for how much you want to spend on interiors when you calculate the total cost spent on your home. Interiors are an essential part of your home because it adds personality to your space. You can choose how your TV unit, wardrobes, bathroom fittings, and much more, need to look. Depending upon your needs, aesthetic preferences, and the quality of these products, the price can be higher or lower.<\/p>\n<p>If you want to use materials like marble, granite, and expensive wood, then it might cost you a hefty sum that could be around Rs. 15-20 lakh. However, if you decide to opt for good quality products in a reasonable price range, then you could complete your interiors at about Rs. 5-6 lakh.<\/li>\n<li>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Goods_and_Service_Tax\"><\/span><strong>Goods and Service Tax<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><img width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4660\" src=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/13.png\" alt=\"goods-service-tax\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/13.png 1200w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/13-300x150.png 300w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/13-1024x512.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/13-768x384.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/>If you purchase an under-construction property in India, then you will be levied the Goods and Services Tax (GST), which is 5%. However, if you choose a ready-to-move-in apartment that has a completion certificate, there will be no GST levied.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Must Read:<\/strong> <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/tax-deductions-on-housing-loans\/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Save up to Rs7* Lakh on Tax Deductions on Housing Loans<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Preferential_Locality_Charge_PLC\"><\/span><strong>Preferential Locality Charge (PLC)<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><img width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4661\" src=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/10.png\" alt=\"preferential-location-charges\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/10.png 1200w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/10-300x150.png 300w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/10-1024x512.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/10-768x384.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/><br \/>\nAs much as garden view, sea view, pool view, or<a href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/bengaluru\/sobha-lake-gardens\/\" rel=\"nofollow\"> lake view apartments<\/a> sound enticing, these come with an additional cost known as the Preferential Locality Charge. When you choose an apartment with a specific view or amenity in mind, it might attract the PLC that can be anywhere between Rs. 100-500 per sq. ft.<\/li>\n<li>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Maintenance_Cost_Deposit\"><\/span><strong>Maintenance Cost Deposit<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><img width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4662\" src=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/6.png\" alt=\"maintenance-cost\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/6.png 1200w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/6-300x150.png 300w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/6-1024x512.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/6-768x384.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/>A maintenance Cost Deposit is collected by the builders to create a corpus fund. The interest on the funds would then be used for common area maintenance purposes. If the interest amount is exhausted, then residents will be charged a maintenance charge for the following month based on the apartment SBA.<\/p>\n<p>The maintenance deposit could be around Rs. 4-5 lakh and can even go up to Rs. 10 lakh, which is to be paid at the time of purchase.<\/li>\n<li>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Miscellaneous_Charges\"><\/span><strong>Miscellaneous Charges<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><img width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4663\" src=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/7.png\" alt=\"miscellaneous-charges\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/7.png 1200w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/7-300x150.png 300w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/7-1024x512.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/7-768x384.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/>Apart from the above charges, you could also incur more expenses. Some of these need not necessarily translate to the cost of your apartment, but it could be an additional expense while buying and moving into your ideal home. This could include the bank loan inspection charges that are part of the home loan amount which you will have to bear as part of the loan repayment, or it could be the expense incurred from hiring packers and movers, etc.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p><strong>Must Read: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/how-to-reduce-your-home-loan-interest-rate\/\" rel=\"nofollow\">How To Reduce Your Home Loan Interest Rate?<\/a><\/strong><\/p>\n<table style=\"height: 375px;\" width=\"696\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"187\"><strong>Additional Costs<\/strong><\/td>\n<td width=\"187\"><strong>Amount<\/strong><\/td>\n<td width=\"187\"><strong>Calculation Basis<\/strong><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"187\">Stamp Duty &amp; Registration Charges<\/td>\n<td width=\"187\">6 lakhs<\/td>\n<td width=\"187\">5% (Stamp Duty) of 1Cr &amp; 1 % of 1Cr (Registration Charge) = 5lakh +1 lakh<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"187\">Brokerage Fee<\/td>\n<td width=\"187\">2 lakhs<\/td>\n<td width=\"187\">Fixed Amount<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"187\">Charges for Additional Parking<\/td>\n<td width=\"187\">4 &#8211; 5 lakh<\/td>\n<td width=\"187\">Fixed amount<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"187\">Interior Designs<\/td>\n<td width=\"187\">5 &#8211; 6 lakh<\/td>\n<td width=\"187\">Depending on preferences<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"187\">GST<\/td>\n<td width=\"187\">5 Lakh<\/td>\n<td width=\"187\">5% of 1Cr.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"187\">PLC<\/td>\n<td width=\"187\">2-10 lakh<\/td>\n<td width=\"187\">Depends on the type of apartment<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"187\">Miscellaneous Charges<\/td>\n<td width=\"187\">20k to 2lakhs<\/td>\n<td width=\"187\">Depending on preferences<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"187\">Maintenance Deposit<\/td>\n<td width=\"187\">5 lakhs<\/td>\n<td width=\"187\">Fixed amount<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p><em>These are the approximate cost suggests for a flat worth Rs. 1 crore in Bengaluru, you will end up paying anywhere between Rs. 25-35 lakh towards all these additional charges. The total cost of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/city\/bengaluru\/\" rel=\"nofollow\">buying a flat in Bangalore<\/a> will be Rs. 1 crore, 35 lakh + GST wherever applicable.\u00a0<\/em><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Conclusion\"><\/span><strong>Conclusion:<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Achieving this milestone of owning your home is a rewarding feeling. However, if you leap carefully, estimating all the expenses incurred, you could keep a watch on your savings as well. This would\u00a0suggest that you are being smart about your real estate investments.<\/p>\n<p>To make this dream a reality, be sure to check our <a href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/city\/bengaluru\/\" rel=\"nofollow\">luxury projects in Bangalore<\/a> that are a class apart and come with an array of amenities.<\/p>\n<p><em>\u00a0<\/em><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Planning to buy a flat in Bangalore? Calculating the total cost of buying a flat is essential for a smooth purchasing experience &amp; a smooth move into the apartment. Our lives are filled with milestones \u2013 some that we achieve effortlessly such as entering adulthood, and some others that we create for ourselves, such as [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":6,"featured_media":4665,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[71],"tags":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v18.4.1 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>How to Calculate The Total Cost of Buying A Flat in Bangalore 2022<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"Calculate the Total Cost of Buying A Flat in Bangalore- know the additional costs that you must consider while calculating the total cost!\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sobha.com\/blog\/total-cost-of-buying-a-flat-in-bangalore\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"How to Calculate The Total Cost of Buying A Flat in Bangalore 2022\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Calculate the Total Cost of Buying A Flat in Bangalore- know the additional costs that you must consider while calculating the total cost!\" \/>\n<meta 